message.content: This command is used to establish a secure shell (SSH) connection with the specified remote server using an SSH key stored in "~/UserKey.pem". The "-C" option enables compression, and the "-L 25900:localhost:5900" option sets up a local port forwarding from your local machine's port 25900 to the remote server's port 5900 (which is typically used for VNC connections). The "user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com" part specifies the remote server's address and username to connect with.
